            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Transactional emails are triggered by a user's individual action and contain information specific to that person — receipts, confirmations, alerts. Marketing emails are sent to a list of subscribers and promote products, content, or offers. Transactional emails do not require opt-in consent under most regulations; marketing emails do. They should be sent from different infrastructure to protect deliverability.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What are examples of transactional emails?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Common examples include: order confirmation emails, shipping notification emails, password reset emails, account creation welcome emails, invoice and payment receipt emails, subscription renewal notices, two-factor authentication codes, appointment confirmation and reminder emails, and account security alerts.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Do transactional emails require opt-in consent?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
